4109  return field_iterator(decl_iterator());
4110  }
4111 
4112  // Whether there are any fields (non-static data members) in this record.
4113  bool field_empty() const {
4114  return field_begin() == field_end();
4115  }
4116 
4117  /// Note that the definition of this type is now complete.
4118  virtual void completeDefinition();
4119 
4120  static bool classof(const Decl *D) { return classofKind(D->getKind()); }
4121  static bool classofKind(Kind K) {

4176 /// Represents a block literal declaration, which is like an
4177 /// unnamed FunctionDecl. For example:
4178 /// ^{ statement-body } or ^(int arg1, float arg2){ statement-body }
4179 class BlockDecl : public Decl, public DeclContext {
4180  // This class stores some data in DeclContext::BlockDeclBits
4181  // to save some space. Use the provided accessors to access it.
4182 public:
4183  /// A class which contains all the information about a particular
4184  /// captured value.
4185  class Capture {
4186  enum {
4187  flag_isByRef = 0x1,
4188  flag_isNested = 0x2
4189  };
4190 
4191  /// The variable being captured.
4192  llvm::PointerIntPair<VarDecl*, 2> VariableAndFlags;
4193 
4194  /// The copy expression, expressed in terms of a DeclRef (or
4195  /// BlockDeclRef) to the captured variable. Only required if the
4196  /// variable has a C++ class type.
4197  Expr *CopyExpr;
4198 
4199  public:
4200  Capture(VarDecl *variable, bool byRef, bool nested, Expr *copy)
4201  : VariableAndFlags(variable,
4202  (byRef ? flag_isByRef : 0) | (nested ? flag_isNested : 0)),
4203  CopyExpr(copy) {}
4204 
4205  /// The variable being captured.
4206  VarDecl *getVariable() const { return VariableAndFlags.getPointer(); }
4207 
4208  /// Whether this is a "by ref" capture, i.e. a capture of a __block
4209  /// variable.
4210  bool isByRef() const { return VariableAndFlags.getInt() & flag_isByRef; }
4211 
4212  bool isEscapingByref() const {
4213  return getVariable()->isEscapingByref();
4214  }
4215 
4216  bool isNonEscapingByref() const {
4217  return getVariable()->isNonEscapingByref();
4218  }
4219 
4220  /// Whether this is a nested capture, i.e. the variable captured
4221  /// is not from outside the immediately enclosing function/block.
4222  bool isNested() const { return VariableAndFlags.getInt() & flag_isNested; }
4223 
4224  bool hasCopyExpr() const { return CopyExpr != nullptr; }
4225  Expr *getCopyExpr() const { return CopyExpr; }
4226  void setCopyExpr(Expr *e) { CopyExpr = e; }
4227  };
4228

4463 /// Describes a module import declaration, which makes the contents
4464 /// of the named module visible in the current translation unit.
4465 ///
4466 /// An import declaration imports the named module (or submodule). For example:
4467 /// \code
4468 /// @import std.vector;
4469 /// \endcode
4470 ///
4471 /// A C++20 module import declaration imports the named module or partition.
4472 /// Periods are permitted in C++20 module names, but have no semantic meaning.
4473 /// For example:
4474 /// \code
4475 /// import NamedModule;
4476 /// import :SomePartition; // Must be a partition of the current module.
4477 /// import Names.Like.this; // Allowed.
4478 /// import :and.Also.Partition.names;
4479 /// \endcode
4480 ///
4481 /// Import declarations can also be implicitly generated from
4482 /// \#include/\#import directives.
4483 class ImportDecl final : public Decl,
4484  llvm::TrailingObjects<ImportDecl, SourceLocation> {
4485  friend class ASTContext;
4486  friend class ASTDeclReader;
4487  friend class ASTReader;
4488  friend TrailingObjects;
4489 
4490  /// The imported module.
4491  Module *ImportedModule = nullptr;
4492 
4493  /// The next import in the list of imports local to the translation
4494  /// unit being parsed (not loaded from an AST file).
4495  ///
4496  /// Includes a bit that indicates whether we have source-location information
4497  /// for each identifier in the module name.
4498  ///
4499  /// When the bit is false, we only have a single source location for the
4500  /// end of the import declaration.
4501  llvm::PointerIntPair<ImportDecl *, 1, bool> NextLocalImportAndComplete;
4502 
4503  ImportDecl(DeclContext *DC, SourceLocation StartLoc, Module *Imported,
4504  ArrayRef<SourceLocation> IdentifierLocs);
4505 
4506  ImportDecl(DeclContext *DC, SourceLocation StartLoc, Module *Imported,
4507  SourceLocation EndLoc);
4508 
4509  ImportDecl(EmptyShell Empty) : Decl(Import, Empty) {}
4510 
4511  bool isImportComplete() const { return NextLocalImportAndComplete.getInt(); }
4512 
4513  void setImportComplete(bool C) { NextLocalImportAndComplete.setInt(C); }
4514 
4515  /// The next import in the list of imports local to the translation
4516  /// unit being parsed (not loaded from an AST file).
4517  ImportDecl *getNextLocalImport() const {
4518  return NextLocalImportAndComplete.getPointer();
4519  }
4520 
4521  void setNextLocalImport(ImportDecl *Import) {
4522  NextLocalImportAndComplete.setPointer(Import);
4523  }
4524 
4525 public:
4526  /// Create a new module import declaration.
4527  static ImportDecl *Create(ASTContext &C, DeclContext *DC,
4528  SourceLocation StartLoc, Module *Imported,
4529  ArrayRef<SourceLocation> IdentifierLocs);
4530 
4531  /// Create a new module import declaration for an implicitly-generated
4532  /// import.
4533  static ImportDecl *CreateImplicit(ASTContext &C, DeclContext *DC,
4534  SourceLocation StartLoc, Module *Imported,
4535  SourceLocation EndLoc);
4536 
4537  /// Create a new, deserialized module import declaration.
4538  static ImportDecl *CreateDeserialized(ASTContext &C, unsigned ID,
4539  unsigned NumLocations);
4540 
4541  /// Retrieve the module that was imported by the import declaration.
4542  Module *getImportedModule() const { return ImportedModule; }
4543 
4544  /// Retrieves the locations of each of the identifiers that make up
4545  /// the complete module name in the import declaration.
4546  ///
4547  /// This will return an empty array if the locations of the individual
4548  /// identifiers aren't available.
4549  ArrayRef<SourceLocation> getIdentifierLocs() const;
4550 
4551  SourceRange getSourceRange() const override LLVM_READONLY;
4552 
4553  static bool classof(const Decl *D) { return classofKind(D->getKind()); }
4554  static bool classofKind(Kind K) { return K == Import; }
4555 };

4557 /// Represents a C++ Modules TS module export declaration.

4559 /// For example:
4560 /// \code
4561 /// export void foo();
4562 /// \endcode
4563 class ExportDecl final : public Decl, public DeclContext {
4564  virtual void anchor();
4565

4568

4570  SourceLocation RBraceLoc;
4571

4574  RBraceLoc(SourceLocation()) {}

4584

4588  if (hasBraces())
4589  return RBraceLoc;

4591  // (if present).
4592  return decls_empty() ? getLocation() : decls_begin()->getEndLoc();
4593  }

4596  return SourceRange(getLocation(), getEndLoc());
4597  }

4602  return static_cast<DeclContext *>(const_cast<ExportDecl*>(D));
4603  }

4624 /// Insertion operator for diagnostics. This allows sending NamedDecl's

4633 template<typename decl_type>
4634 void Redeclarable<decl_type>::setPreviousDecl(decl_type *PrevDecl) {
4635  // Note: This routine is implemented here because we need both NamedDecl
4636  // and Redeclarable to be defined.
4637  assert(RedeclLink.isFirst() &&
4638  "setPreviousDecl on a decl already in a redeclaration chain");
4639 
4640  if (PrevDecl) {
4641  // Point to previous. Make sure that this is actually the most recent
4642  // redeclaration, or we can build invalid chains. If the most recent
4643  // redeclaration is invalid, it won't be PrevDecl, but we want it anyway.
4644  First = PrevDecl->getFirstDecl();
4645  assert(First->RedeclLink.isFirst() && "Expected first");
4646  decl_type *MostRecent = First->getNextRedeclaration();
4647  RedeclLink = PreviousDeclLink(cast<decl_type>(MostRecent));
4648 
4649  // If the declaration was previously visible, a redeclaration of it remains
4650  // visible even if it wouldn't be visible by itself.
4651  static_cast<decl_type*>(this)->IdentifierNamespace |=
4652  MostRecent->getIdentifierNamespace() &
4653  (Decl::IDNS_Ordinary | Decl::IDNS_Tag | Decl::IDNS_Type);
4654  } else {
4655  // Make this first.
4656  First = static_cast<decl_type*>(this);
4657  }
4658 
4659  // First one will point to this one as latest.
4660  First->RedeclLink.setLatest(static_cast<decl_type*>(this));
4661 
4662  assert(!isa<NamedDecl>(static_cast<decl_type*>(this)) ||
4663  cast<NamedDecl>(static_cast<decl_type*>(this))->isLinkageValid());
4664 }
4665

4672 inline bool IsEnumDeclComplete(EnumDecl *ED) {
4673  return ED->isComplete();

4676 /// Check if the given decl is scoped.

4679 /// Type.h and Decl.h.

4682 }
